OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGove confident leasehold   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbill will pass by election 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Housing Secretary Michael Gove has said
OL,6, he is confident a bill reforming the   
OL,7, leasehold system in England and Wales  
OL,8, will pass by the next general election.
OL,10,FThe bill, which would ban leaseholds   
OL,11,Ffor new houses but not flats, is due to
OL,12,Fbe introduced in Parliament later.     
OL,14,FIt would also make it easier and       
OL,15,Fcheaper for homeowners to extend their 
OL,16,Flease or buy their freehold.           
OL,18,FUnder the current system leaseholders  
OL,19,Foften have to pay ground rent and      
OL,20,Fexpensive maintenance charges.         
